panels.content:
# Throughput Trends

This dashboard display an overview of how throughput changes over time 
For each benchmark you can compare throughput metrics for a specific
number of terminals. You can also compare a throughput metric across 
different terminal values. Feel free to mix and match, but be warned
the charts can get overwhelming pretty fast.

targets.rawSql:
SELECT
  "time" AS "time",
  (metrics->>'throughput')::jsonb::text::numeric AS "terminals = 1",
  git_commit_id
FROM oltpbench_results
WHERE
  $__timeFilter("time") AND
  benchmark_type = ${benchmark_type} AND
  terminals IN (${terminals}) AND
  terminals = 1
ORDER BY time

SELECT
  to_char(time, 'Mon DD') as "Date",
  (metrics->>'throughput')::jsonb::text::numeric AS "Throughput",
  (FIRST_VALUE((metrics->>'throughput')::jsonb::text::numeric) OVER(PARTITION BY terminals order by time desc) -
  FIRST_VALUE((metrics->>'throughput')::jsonb::text::numeric) OVER(PARTITION BY terminals order by time asc)) / 
  FIRST_VALUE((metrics->>'throughput')::jsonb::text::numeric) OVER(PARTITION BY terminals order by time desc) * 100 as "Change %"
FROM oltpbench_results
WHERE
  $__timeFilter("time") AND
  benchmark_type = ${benchmark_type} AND
  terminals IN (${terminals})
ORDER BY "Date" DESC
